<html>

<title>Robert G. Morrison, Special Assistant to the President</title>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/whois/whois.gif">
</center>

<p>

<center>

<h2><font size=+3>R</font>obert <font size=+3>G</font>. 
<font size=+3>M</font>orrison</h2>

<h3>Special Assistant to the President & Policy Analyst</h3>

<p><hr size=3 width=50%><p>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/photos/frc9.gif">
<p><hr size=3 width=50%><p>

</center>

<p>

Mr. Morrison's articles have been published in <I>Focus on the Family</I> 
magazine, <I>Citizen World</I> magazine, <I>The Catholic Register</I>, 
and <I>The Lutheran Witness</I>.  He represented the Lutheran Church - 
Missouri Synod's president in Washington.

<p>

Mr. Morrison was a special assistant in the U.S. Department of Education 
prior to LCMS.  His responsibilities included research and writing on 
such projects as <I>The Family: America's Future</I> report, The 
National Conference on Youth Suicide, the Hatch Amendment, and Global 
Studies.  He served on the National Advisory Board on Child Abuse and 
Neglect and on the Interagency Task Force on Rural America.

<p>

From 1982-1984, Mr. Morrison was Executive Director of Connecticut 
Citizens Concerned for Life, an agency which promoted public 
discussion of the relationship between public policy and medical 
and social issues.

<p>

Also an experienced educator, Mr. Morrison taught high school history 
in his native New York state and history and political science at the 
college level in Washington state.  His teaching credits include 
adult education at the Klallam Indian Reservation in Port Gamble, 
Washington.

<p>

Mr. Morrison is a veteran of the U.S. Coast Guard, where he served as 
a Russian language interpreter and communications officer aboard the 
Cutter <I>Boutwell</I>. He received his B.A. and M.A. degrees in 
government and foreign affairs from the University of Virginia.  He 
has also done graduate work in history and journalism at the 
University of Washington.

<p>

Mr. Morrison is married and the father of two children.

<p><HR SIZE = 3 WIDTH = 60%><p>

<center>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrip.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrip.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
