<a href="#comments">Selected Comments</a><P>
<b>Question:</b> Will the Million Man March increase or decrease racial tension?<P>Increase: 80%<br>Decrease: 20%
<P><b>Question:</b> Do you believe that the Million Man March was meant to be a wake-up call to our nation's leadership?<P>Yes: 51%<br>No: 49%
<p><b>Question</b> Do you believe affirmative action is an important issue for Congress to address?<P>Yes: 93:<br>No: 7%
<p><b>Question</b> Will any reform come about because of the Million Man March?<p>Yes: 2%<br>No: 98%
<P><b>Question</b> Do you believe the Republicans or the Democrats are more serious about ensuring fairness in hiring practices?<P>Republicans: 95%<br>Democrats: 5%
<p><b>Question</b> Is affirmative action necessary in today's America?<P>Yes: 6%<br>No: 94%
<p><b>Question</b> Does affirmative action, as implemented today, create equality?<p>Yes: 2%<br>No: 98%
<p><b>Question</b><i>Can</i> an affirmative action program create equality?<P>Yes: 95%<br>No: 5%
<p><b>Question</b>Should affirmative action programs be abolished?<P>Yes: 95%<br>No: 5%
<p><b>Question</b>If affirmative action reform does not pass this year, who will you hold responsible?<P>Republicans: 43%<br>Democrats: 57%<p><hr><P>
