<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>At a Glance: More about debis AG</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../group_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/komp_kl.gif"></A><A HREF="debis_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>More about debis AG</B></FONT><P><TABLE><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380>By offering sophisticated, high-value "one-stop" services, the Berlin-based Daimler-Benz InterServices (debis) AG is pursuing its strategy of expansion and further enhancing its market position. Over 200 branches in 23 countries of the world are a clear sign of the international orientation of debis's seven divisions. In strategic alliances with other leading companies - such as <A HREF="http://www.cgs.fr">Cap Gemini Sogeti</A>, the biggest supplier of IT services in Europe which is independent of the manufacturers, and which also operates in the USA - debis is opening up new markets, winning international customers and guaranteeing the highest possible level of service to its customers all over the world. In the words of Dr. Klaus Mangold, Chairman of the Board of Management of debis AG: "Through our customer-focused expansion of our range of services and by opening up new areas of business - for example in the fields of multimedia and modern traffic management - we are exploiting the vast potential for growth that exists in the service sector, in order to be involved in the markets of the future as a provider of modern services."<p>Daimler-Benz InterServices (debis) AG, with its seven business divisions - Systemhaus, Financial Services, Insurance Brokerage, Trading, Marketing Services, Telecommunications and Media Services and Real Estate Management - is the service undertaking of the Daimler-Benz Group. Established on July 1st 1990, the company has achieved substantial growth during the first five years of its existence, increasing its turnover from around DM 4 billion to some DM 11,6 billion (1995). This means that debis's turnover has been multiplied almost threefold since the company was established. The number of employees has risen over the same period from 3,600 to 10,196. Almost 2,000 of these work in debis's foreign branches. J&uuml;rgen Gembus, the member of the Board of Management of debis AG responsible for personnel and mobile communications services, says: "Crucial to debis's competitiveness are the level of qualification of its staff and their high degree of commitment. This shows that in a customer-focused service undertaking above all, investment in staff training is the key to success."<p>By having its headquarters in Berlin, debis AG demonstrates its total confidence in Germany's future as a service industry location. The debis Group's most important mission is to take over the responsibility for services on behalf of its customers, thereby allowing them to concentrate fully and completely on their core activities.<p>The various ranges of services offered are designed to be modular in structure, so that the company can offer both tailor-made individual packages and overall integrated solutions - according to the requirements of each particular customer. This is also the meaning of the debis logo, which represents the dynamic concentration of individual services into a single organised system.</TABLE><P><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="debis2_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../group_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>At a Glance</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="debis_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Up</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>   <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 04/11/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
