<HTML>

<HEAD><TITLE>At a Glance: Daimler-Benz</TITLE></HEAD>



<BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF">

<P>



<CENTER>



<A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../group_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/komp_kl.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../mercedes/mb_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> 

<A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A>

<BR>



<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P>



<FONT SIZE=+3><B>Daimler-Benz</B></FONT>

<P>



<TABLE>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><IMG width=200 height=160 SRC="pics/daimler.gif"><BR>

<TD WIDTH=20>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275>

Daimler-Benz is the largest industrial group in the whole of Europe. Combining a powerful blend of expertise and experience, Daimler-Benz's business interests extend from the field of traffic and transport to the production of components and systems, and include the provision of services associated with its key business sectors. With more than 310,000 employees worldwide (December, 1995), the company had a turnover of more than 100 billion DM in 1995.

<TR><TD>



<TR>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275>

1996 and 1997 are to be years of transition at Daimler-Benz. With the AEG corporation to be amalgamated into the Daimler-Benz AG by mid-1996, the aim is to tighten-up the business portfolio and improve the overall profit structure. Railway systems, microelectronics and postal automation are to be controlled directly by Daimler-Benz with diesel drive systems coming under the industrial control of Mercedes-Benz. Now that financial support for Fokker has been terminated, Daimler-Benz Aerospace's activities will concentrate essentially upon the Airbus project.<br>

<TD WIDTH=20>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275>
In the future, too, the company will continue to trim its structure so as to create an effective synergy of technical know-how and corporate engagement: Mercedes-Benz will concentrate on its role as a manufacturer of passenger cars and commercial vehicles; Daimler-Benz Aerospace on activities in the areas of aircraft and space systems, defence technology, alongside the production of civil systems; Daimler-Benz Interservices (debis) on its role as the supplier of sophisticated services.

</TABLE>

<p><br>



<IMG WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_250.gif"><P>



<TABLE>

<TR>

<TD ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275 valign=top><A HREF="bofm/bofm_e.htm"><font size=+1><I><B>The Board of Management</B></I></FONT></A><BR>

<TD width=20>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275 valign=top><A HREF="data_e.htm"><font size=+1><I><B>Facts and Figures</B></FONT></I></A><BR>

</TABLE>

<p><br>



<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P>



<TABLE>

<TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550>

