<HTML>

<HEAD><TITLE>At a Glance: Railway Systems</TITLE></HEAD>



<BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF">

<P>



<CENTER>



<A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../group_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/komp_kl.gif"></A>

<A HREF="micro_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> 

<A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A>

<BR>



<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P>



<FONT SIZE=+3><B>Railway Systems</B></FONT>

<P>



<TABLE>



<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><IMG ALIGN=Right VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=160 border=0 SRC="pics/adtranz.gif"><BR>



<TD WIDTH=20>



<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275>Daimler-Benz and Asea Brown Boveri AG (ABB) have merged operations in the rail sector and joined forces to form Adtranz. The result of a joint 50%-50% holding, Adtranz can profit from ABB's leading role in the field of microelectronics and from the exceptional position enjoyed by Daimler-Benz in the areas of mechanical engineering and transport systems. Adtranz is therefore perfectly poised to generate the innovative and world-beating solutions needed to solve the transport problems of today.<BR>



<TR><TD><br>



<TR>





<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275>

The product range on offer at Adtranz incorporates just about everything that can run on rails: electric and diesel locomotives, high-speed trains, intercity and local trains, underground and city transit systems, streetcars as well as fully-automated passenger transport systems, freight cars, train security systems, transport management systems, rail supply systems, and, finally, maintenance and repair services.<br>



<TD WIDTH=20>



<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275>



Adtranz has an extremely high profile worldwide and is active in Australia, Asia, India, Europe, North and South America, and Africa. Made up a large number of smaller, customer-oriented branches, the group has a decentralized organizational structure. With the help of the support and cooperation they enjoy from technology centers based throughout the world, these locally operating companies are then able to offer an optimal package of attractively-priced know-how and expertise designed to match the their customers' needs.<P>

</TABLE>

<IMG WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_250.gif"><P>



<A HREF="http://www.adtranz.com"><I><font size=+1><B>to the Adtranz WWW-Server</B></FONT></I></A><BR>


<p><br>


<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P>



<TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550>

<H5>

<A HREF="rail_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A>

