<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>At a Glance: Recognition and Sorting Systems</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../group_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/komp_kl.gif"></A><A HREF="../daimler/db_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+3><B>Recognition and Sorting Systems</B></FONT><P><TABLE><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><IMG SRC="pics/postal.gif"><BR><TD WIDTH=20><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275>The Postal Automation Division manufactures and sells sorting systems for postal services, commercial and industrial users worldwide.<BR><TR><TD><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275>Managed by AEG ElectroCom International, Inc., Irving, Texas, the division enjoys a more than 50% share of the world market for postal sortation systems, with over 8,500 such systems operating daily in over 25 countries on five continents.The systems are distinguished by a combination of  high-precision mechanics, advanced information technology and customized application software. The spectrum of products ranges broadly from sorting systems for standard letters, flats, small parcels and parcels with automatic, high-speed address readers to  recognition systems<BR><TD WIDTH=20><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275>for automated data, text and image capture. From stand-alone systems to complete turn-key sorting centers, any customer requirement can be accommodated.  Services include not only advanced instruction and computer-based training systems, consultancy and contract maintenance, but prime contracting as well.The corporate business units, AEG Electrocom GmbH in Constance, Germany, Electrocom Automation, L.P. in Arlington,Texas and AEG Hitachi Postal Automation Ltd., Tokyo, Japan,  employ more than 2,500 people. Group sales in 1995 topped  606 million German Marks. <BR></TABLE><P><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="postal_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../group_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>At a Glance</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../daimler/db_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 04/11/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
