<HTML><HEAD>  <TITLE>Daimler-Benz to sell AEG Electrocom to Siemens</TITLE>  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac"></HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" LINK="#2060a0" VLINK="#606060"ALINK="#e0e0ff"><P ALIGN=CENTER><!--NOEDIT--><center><!--/NOEDIT--><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="89" HEIGHT="33" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/newskl.gif"BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="61107_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <BR><IMG SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif" WIDTH="592" HEIGHT="16" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Daimler-Benz to sell AEG Electrocom to Siemens</FONT></B></P><p><P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="380"><P><I>Stuttgart / Constance, January 13, 1997</I><BR>Daimler-Benz AG will sell its wholly owned subsidiaries AEG Electrocom GmbH, Constance, Germany, and AEG ElectroCom International Inc. (ECA), Irving, Texas, to the Siemens Automation division, based in Nuremberg, Germany. With this sale, Daimler-Benz largely completes its effort to focus the group's business on traffic, transport and services. Following the sale, the Daimler-Benz group will be comprised of 23 business units compared to 35 in mid-1995.<p>The companies will be taken over in full by Siemens. The acquisition will enter into effect retrospectively from January 1, 1997, according to statements made by the two companies on January 13. The contracts have already been signed. The take-over is subject to the approval of the cartel authorities. The companies have not made any statement concerning purchase price.<p>The business unit Recognition and Sorting Systems in which the worldwide activities of AEG Electrocom are housed has an excellent position on the market and is performing successfully. However, since the dissolution of AEG in 1996, this sector has no longer ranked among the fields of activity which now constitute the focus of the Daimler-Benz group. When Daimler-Benz took over the US company ECA in 1994, it already emphasised that it was hoping to find a suitable investor. With AEG Electrocom, Siemens will acquire the perfect complement to the existing activities in its Automation division.<p>AEG Electrocom is a leading supplier in the field of sorting and recognition systems for postal automation. In 1995 the company recorded worldwide sales of approximately DM 650 mill. Sales for 1996 are expected to total approximately DM 1 billion. In recent years the American market has accounted for around 70 % of total sales. Electrocom employs a workforce of just under 3,000 worldwide, around 40 % of these in the USA and around 60 % in Germany. Approximately 10,000 Electrocom letter sorting systems are currently in use in 29 countries around the world.</TD></TR></TABLE></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><BR><IMG SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif" WIDTH="592" HEIGHT="16" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE><TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH="550"><H5><A HREF="70113_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch&nbsp;]</I> </A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home&nbsp;]</I></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>News&nbsp;]</I> </A><A HREF="61107_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next&nbsp;]</I></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search&nbsp;]</I> </A><AHREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog&nbsp;]</I> </A><A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help&nbsp;]</I></A></H5></TD></TR></TABLE></P><ADDRESS ALIGN=CENTER>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 01/13/1996</ADDRESS></BODY></HTML>
