/B>, Vice President Advanced Technologies, Adtranz- ABB Daimler-Benz Transportation GmbH<br><p><br><TR><TD WIDTH=120><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=450 valign=top><font size=+1><A HREF="ross/ross_e.htm"><i><B>Successful technical cooperation between Germany and the USA<br>The acrobat in the sky: the X-31 experimental aircraft - a breakthrough in aviation engineeringFull manoeuvrability even when stalling</B></i></A></font><p><B><A HREF="persons/ross_e.htm">Dipl-Ing. Hannes Ross</A></B>, Head of pre-development in the military aircraft division of Daimler-Benz Aerospace AG<br><p><br><TR><TD WIDTH=120><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=450 valign=top><font size=+1><A HREF="hahn/hahn_e.htm"><i><B>A new approach to greater utilisation of road capacity:the electronic drawbar for commercial vehicle convoys</B></i></A></font><p><B><A HREF="persons/hahn_e.htm">Stefan Hahn</A></B>, Scientific head of the Auxiliary Systems department, Daimler-Benz AG<br><p><br><TR><TD WIDTH=120><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=450 valign=top><font size=+1><A HREF="heinri/heinri_e.htm"><i><B>Car telephones that obey every word-voice system jointly developed by Mercedes-Benz, Dasa and Daimler-Benz Research permits phoning at the wheel without risk</B></i></A></font><p><B><A HREF="persons/heinri_e.htm">Dr. Christian Heinrich</A></B>, Head, Dialog and Assistance Systems in Preliminary Development, Electronics / Systems, Mercedes-Benz Passenger Car Development, and<br><B><A HREF="persons/stamml_e.htm">Dr.-Ing. Walter Stammler</A></B>, Head of the Signal Processing Department in Profit Center VS6 of Daimler-Benz Aerospace AG<br><p><br><TR><TD WIDTH=120><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=450 valign=top><font size=+1><A HREF="danner/danner_e.htm"><i><B>Distance recognition and distance control in road traffic<br>Cars will soon be capable of perception and reaction</B></i></A></font><p><B><A HREF="persons/danner_e.htm">Bernd Danner</A></B>, Project manager for series development of the distance control Tempomat, Mercedes-B