<head>
<title>Consolidated Interim Report: Daimler-Benz Group</title>

</head>

<body background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" text="#000000" link="#2060A0" vlink="#606060" alink="#E0E0FF">
<p align=center><a href="../../index_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/db_home.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=89 height=33></a> <a href="../facts_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/factskl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="merced_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/menu_rig.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../search/search_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/db_such.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/mailkl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../help/help_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/helpkl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <br>
<img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
<p align=center><font size=5><b>Daimler-Benz Group </b></font><sup><font size=1><b>1)</b></font></sup></p>
<div align=center><center>
<table>
<tr><td valign=bottom><font size=2>DM amounts in millions</font> </td><td></td><td align=right valign=bottom width=130><b>01-09/96</b></td><td></td><td align=right width=130><b>01-09/95</b></td></tr>
<tr><td align=right valign=top width=220></td><td></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Revenues</strong></td><td></td><td align=right><strong>75,913</strong></td><td></td><td align=right><strong>72,782</strong></td></tr>
<tr><td>EU-Market </td><td></td><td align=right>46,311</td><td></td><td align=right>43,429</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;&#160;&#160;Germany </td><td></td><td align=right>27,984</td><td></td><td align=right>26,747</td></tr>
<tr><td>&#160;&#160;&#160;EU excluding Germany </td><td></td><td align=right>18,327</td><td></td><td align=right>16,682</td></tr>
<tr><td>USA </td><td></td><td align=right>13,863</td><td></td><td align=right>12,718</td></tr>
<tr><td>Other markets </td><td></td><td align=right>15,739</td><td></td><td align=right>16,635</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Employees </b><font size=2><b>(9/30)</b></font><b> </b></td><td></td><td align=right><strong>290,031</strong></td><td></td><td align=right><strong>291,226</strong></td><td><sup><font size=1>*)</font></sup></td></tr>
<tr><td>Germany </td><td></td><td align=right>223,106</td><td></td><td align=right>226,701</td><td align=right><sup><font size=1>*)</font></sup> </td></tr>
<tr><td>Foreign </td><td></td><td align=right>66,925</td><td></td><td align=right>64,525</td><td align=right><sup><font size=1>*)</font></sup> </td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p></p>
</center></div>
<div align=center><center>
<table width=500>
<tr><td><font size=2>*) Personnel figures as of 9/30/95 have been adjusted to take account<br>
 of significant changes in consolidation.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td></tr>
</table>
<p></p>
</center></div>
<div align=center><center>
<table>
<tr><td valign=top width=380>In the first nine months of 1996, Daimler-Benz generated 
revenues totaling DM 75.9 billion. After making adjustments 
for changes within the consolidated group, this represents an 
11% increase over the first nine months of the previous year. 
All of the corporate units and directly managed business units 
contributed to the expansion, which was experienced in almost 
every market. Mercedes-Benz remained the principal source 
of consolidated revenues, contributing just under three 
quarters of the total; debis contributed 12% and Dasa 10%. 
The remaining 7% were distributed among the directly 
managed business units Rail Systems, Microelectronics, Diesel 
Engines, and Recognition and Sorting Systems. In addition to 
the growth in revenues, the positive development of profits in 
the first half year continued.<p>On September 30, Daimler-Benz had 290,031 employees 
worldwide, of which just under 11,000 represent the pro rata 
share (50%) of the Adtranz joint venture founded by 
Daimler-Benz and ABB at the beginning of 1996. At 
Mercedes-Benz and Dasa, and in the Microelectronics and 
Diesel Engines divisions, the number of employees declined as 
compared to September 1995, while the number rose 
markedly at debis in particular.</p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
