<head>
<title>Consolidated Interim Report: Daimler-Benz InterServices (debis)</title>

</head>

<body background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" text="#000000" link="#2060A0" vlink="#606060" alink="#E0E0FF">
<p align=center><a href="../../index_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/db_home.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=89 height=33></a> <a href="../facts_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/factskl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="direct_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/menu_rig.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../search/search_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/db_such.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/mailkl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../help/help_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/helpkl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <br>
<img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
<p align=center><font size=5><b>Daimler-Benz InterServices (debis)</b></font> </p>
<div align=center><center>
<table>
<tr><td valign=bottom><font size=2>DM amounts in millions</font> </td><td></td><td align=right valign=bottom width=130><b>01-09/96</b></td><td></td><td align=right width=130><b>01-09/95</b></td></tr>
<tr><td align=right valign=top width=220></td><td></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Revenues </td><td></td><td align=right>9,758</td><td></td><td align=right>8,572</td></tr>
<tr><td>Employees <font size=2>(9/30)</font> </td><td></td><td align=right>11,305</td><td></td><td align=right>10,169</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p></p>
</center></div>
<div align=center><center>
<table>
<tr><td valign=top width=380>Daimler-Benz InterServices (debis) continued its dynamic 
growth with a double-digit increase in revenues. As part of its 
concentration on core businesses, debis withdraw from its 
Marketing Services activities.<p>The 14% expansion in business to DM 9.8 billion was 
primarily contributed by the divisions Systemhaus, Financial 
Services, and Telecommunications and Media Services. 
Systemhaus generated a 14% increase to DM 1.7 billion, due 
above all to the computer communication services unit and the 
software sector. At DM 6.3 billion, Financial Services 
contributed the largest share in revenues at debis, surpassing 
the previous year&#146;s total by 12%. In the Telecommunication 
and Media Services division, mobile communication services 
once again reported especially vigorous growth (up 70%). The 
Insurance Brokerage and Real Estate Management divisions 
are steadily developing and successively expanding their 
market positions.</p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
