</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Diesel Engines</strong></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr>
<tr><td>Revenues</td><td></td><td align=right>1,069</td><td></td><td align=right>944</td></tr>
<tr><td>Incoming orders</td><td></td><td align=right>1,197</td><td></td><td align=right>1,048</td></tr>
<tr><td>Employees <font size=2>(9/30)</font> </td><td></td><td align=right>5,613</td><td></td><td align=right>5,697</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Recognition and Sorting Systems</strong></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr>
<tr><td>Revenues</td><td></td><td align=right>704</td><td></td><td align=right>352</td></tr>
<tr><td>Incoming orders</td><td></td><td align=right>739</td><td></td><td align=right>770</td></tr>
<tr><td>Employees <font size=2>(9/30)</font> </td><td></td><td align=right>3,283</td><td></td><td align=right>2,615</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=5><hr>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p></p>
</center></div>
<div align=center><center>
<table>
<tr><td valign=top width=380>In the Rail Systems division, the pro rata share in revenues of 
the joint venture ABB Daimler-Benz Transportation (Adtranz) 
was DM 1.9 billion. Incoming orders totaled DM 2.1 billion; 
additional large orders from China, Singapore, Turkey, and 
Thailand were received in October.<p>In Microelectronics, revenues in the first nine months of 1996 
reached DM 1.8 billion, an 11% increase over the previous 
year. The growth in revenues was especially pronounced in the 
motor vehicle electronics and gas generator sectors (up 26% 
and 21% respectively); both the semiconductor and the 
microsystems sectors reported a moderate 3% expansion. 
Incoming orders were not as high as in the first nine months of 
1995 (down 4%). This was above all caused by the weak 
semi-conductor market.</p>
<p>In the Diesel Engines division, revenues and incoming orders 
rose by 13% and 14% respectively. For the most part, this 
was due to the intensified expansion of the emerging business 
segments decentralized energy systems and commercial ships. 
But business in the navy vessel and military vehicle sectors also 
surpassed the previous year&#146;s volume.</p>
<p>In Recognition and Sorting Systems, revenues have doubled 
due to the invoicing of large orders, most notably those placed 
by the US and German postal services. Once again, incoming 
orders were higher than revenues, and additional large orders 
are expected for the fourth quarter of 1996.</p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
