<html>

<head>
<title>Consolidated Interim Report: Outlook</title>

</head>

<body background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" text="#000000" link="#2060A0" vlink="#606060" alink="#E0E0FF">
<p align=center><a href="../../index_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/db_home.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=89 height=33></a> <a href="../facts_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/factskl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../facts_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/menu_rig.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../search/search_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/db_such.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/mailkl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <a href="../../help/help_e.htm"><img src="../../icons/helpkl.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=54 height=44></a> <br>
<img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
<p align=center><font size=5><b>Outlook</b></font> </p>
<div align=center><center>
<table>
<tr><td valign=top width=380>The revival of business achieved in the first nine months of 
1996 will most likely continue in the final quarter of the year. 
For the year as a whole, we therefore anticipate our business 
volume to top DM 105 billion, a definite increase over the 
previous year&#146;s total, which after making adjustments for 
changes in the consolidated group was DM 96.9 billion. All of 
the corporate units and directly managed business units will 
contribute to this growth.<p>In the passenger car sector at Mercedes-Benz, sales are 
expected to reach well over 600,000 vehicles. Because of the 
success of the new vans in Western Europe, sales in the 
Commercial Vehicle division will again surpass the 1995 
record of 320,000 units. The recently launched Actros should 
give new impetus in the fourth quarter to the difficult truck 
business in Western Europe.</p>
<p>After making adjustments for structural changes, Dasa is 
expecting a revival of business for the current fiscal year 
primarily in the civil sector.</p>
<p>Because of the favorable order situation at debis and in the 
directly managed business units, we anticipate a double-digit 
increase in revenues in these segments for 1996.</p>
<p>Thanks to the clear advancements in productivity that we have 
realized in the various sectors of the Daimler-Benz group, and 
due to the more favorable currency relations, the higher 
business volume in almost every division is accompanied by a 
favorable development in profits. In the truck business in 
Western Europe and the Microelectronics division we have 
introduced measures to improve results, which will become 
effective as from 1997. We continue to expect that the 
group&#146;s profit will further improve in the second half of 
1996</p>
<p>.<i>November 1996<br>
Daimler-Benz Aktiengesellschaft </i></p>
<p><i>The Board of Management</i> </p>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<p align=center><img src="../../lines/db_592.gif" align=bottom width=592 height=16></p>
