<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Daimler-Benz Research and Technology</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY background="../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF">
<P>

<CENTER>

<A HREF="../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../icons/db_home.gif"></A>
<A HREF="news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/researkl.gif"></A>
<A HREF="../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/db_such.gif"></A>
<A HREF="../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> 
<A HREF="../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/helpkl.gif"></A>
<BR>

<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../lines/db_592.gif"><P>

<FONT SIZE=+3><B>Daimler-Benz<br> Research and Technology</B></FONT>
<P>

<table>
<TR>
<TD>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=160 border=0 SRC="pics/ulm.gif"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=160 SRC="../icons/abstand.gif">
<TD VALIGN=BOTTOM><B><FONT SIZE=-1>The Daimler-Benz <br>Research Centre in Ulm</FONT></B>
<TR><TD><BR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD  WIDTH=380>At group level, Daimler-Benz carries out application-oriented research, supports
technology transfer within the group and contributes its technological competence to strategic decisions.
<P>

The research sectors F1, F2, F3 and F4 work specifically for the corporate units. The accent here is on research topics related to the products and business of the corporate units. The interdisciplinary research activities on the other hand, for example in the fields of traffic, materials, microelectronics and microsystems, informatics, Production and environment research and the relationship between research, technology and society are oriented primarily to group-wide research topics. Group-level research is carried out at locations in Berlin, Frankfurt, Friedrichshafen, Munich, Stuttgart, Ulm and <A HREF="http://www.rtna.daimlerbenz.com">Palo Alto</A> (California), Portland (Oregon), Bangalore (India) and Shanhai (China).
<P>

The Technology Division of the group is responsible for technology and information management and for assisting the technological integration and strategic orientation of the group.
<P>
<br>
<H3>Important fields of research</H3>

<LI>Engines and propulsion systems
<LI>Methods and tools of vehicle design
<LI>Vehicle systems
<LI>Man and the motor vehicle
<LI>Traffic and traffic environment
<LI>Energy transformation
<LI>Microelectronics and microsystems
<LI>Materials/New materials
<LI>Automation and drive systems
<LI>Information technology
<LI>Production and environment research
<LI>Society and Technology
</TABLE>
<p><br>

<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../lines/db_592.gif"><P>

