<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Plants monitor air quality</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="61210_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Plants monitor air quality</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><A HREF="pics/61217.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/61217.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif"><i>Stuttgart, December 17, 1996</i><br>Whether it's ozone in the air or nitrates in the soil, whether it's pollutants in car exhaust or foreign substances in foodstuffs: there is nothing more impersonal and perplexing than limit values expressed in the form of cold figures. After all, who can gain a lucid impression of the burden placed on nature and the environment simply by studying columns of figures?<p>Mercedes-Benz, a corporate unit of Daimler-Benz AG, is using various plants at its manufacturing site in Sindelfingen to assess in clearly visible form the effects of pol-lutants in the air: every fourteen days, the scientists examine tomato shrubs, spinach and nasturtiums for the effects of solvent emissions from the painting facilities.<p>The first stage of the project - the "process engineering" - was concerned with the search for suitable indicator plants. This was followed by the actual bio-monitoring, i.e. the process of surveillance and assessment of the waste air from the painting facility, carried out by these plants. <p>At six different locations - directly on the site and in the immediate vicinity - some-thing of a hobby gardener's paradise is now keeping a watchful eye on air quality. The positive result of the long-term surveillance: none of the test plants has suffered any damage which could be traced back to the Mercedes-Benz paining facility. Even at sites subject to maximum environmental load, the concentration of noxious sub-stances has been found to be too low by a factor of 50 to 100 to cause any damage to the plants.</TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="61217_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="61210_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 12/17/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
