</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Recovery instead of disposal</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="61008_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Recovery instead of disposal</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><A HREF="pics/61015.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/61015.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif"><i>Stuttgart, October 15, 1996</i><br>Pat-a-cake, pat-a-cake, baker's man, bake me a cake as fast as you can." In this case, however, it is not the backer who is calling, but an employee from the foundry. In this process, the casting moulds for the metal components are baked from so-called core sand. The interest of the engineers from the Daimler-Benz corporate unit Mercedes-Benz focuses not so much on the baking process itself, but rather on the waste air produced.<p>The waste air from the foundry contains the gaseous catalyst dimethyl isopropyl amine in high concentrations; this substance serves to expedite the hardening of the core sand, binding agents and resins used in the baking process. At present, an acid scrubber in the waste air stream diverts the amine into a saline solution for subsequent disposal. The environmental engi-neers are currently devising a method of recovering the catalyst from the waste air and returning it to the baking process.<p>The test rig comprises several units. Preliminary filters first of all remove dust, dirt and excess binding and hardening agents from the foundry waste air, which then flows through a rotary adsorption unit containing polyurethane foam on an active carbon base. The amine accumulates on the active carbon foam, which has an immense surface area, and the purified air is discharged into the atmosphere.<p>When air at a temperature of about 150 &#176;C is added to a certain section of the rotary adsorption unit, the gaseous amine can be separated from the active carbon foam. Before the amine can be returned to the baking process to serve as a catalyst, however, it must be completely free of water. The engineers achieve this by means of a downstream dehumidification wheel, which operates on the same principle as the adsorption unit.<p>The final phase is the recovery of the catalyst. A refrigerating machine cools the gas stream containing amine to -40 &#176;C, and the amine condenses. The engineers can thus recover about eighty percent of the amine in liquid form.<p>Having successfully completed preliminary tests on a laboratory scale, the unit must now prove its mettle under conditions of everyday operation in the Mettingen iron foundry of the Mercedes-Benz Untert&uuml;rkheim plant. The declared aim of the scientists is to reach at least break-even point; in other words, the costs of recovery and reuse of the amine are not to exceed the procurement price of the catalyst plus the waste disposal costs.</TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="61015_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="61008_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 10/15/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
