<HTML><HEAD>  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">  <TITLE>Auxiliary motors on the basis of magnetic resistance</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" LINK="#2060a0" VLINK="#606060"ALINK="#e0e0ff"><P ALIGN=CENTER><!--NOEDIT--><center><!--/NOEDIT--><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="89" HEIGHT="33" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="60923_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <BR><IMG SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif" WIDTH="592" HEIGHT="16" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Auxiliary motors<BR>on the basis of magnetic resistance</FONT></B></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Old hat, new applications: <BR>the reluctance engine</FONT></B></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0"><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="380"><P><A HREF="61001.jpg"><IMG SRC="pics/61001.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" vspace="3"hspace="-2" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="80" BORDER="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A><IMG SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="3" HSPACE="-2" WIDTH="6"HEIGHT="80" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><I>Stuttgart, October 1, 1996</I><BR>If we are asked &quot;How many power units does a car need?&quot; we aretempted to give the spontaneous answer &quot;One&quot;. To put it mildly,however, this reply is somewhat wide of the mark: the engine which propelsthe vehicle is supplemented by up to 25 electric mo-tors which contributeto driving operation and ride comfort.</P><P>The electrically operated windows, the air conditioner fan and the fuelpump are just three ex-amples of the numerous systems operated by electricmotors.</P><P>The Daimler-Benz researchers are using a highly elegant variant of theauxiliary engine in the coolant circuit of the Necar II fuel cell vehicle:the reluctance motor. Familiar since 1859, this unit has the simplest mechanicaldesign of all electric motors. &quot;Reluctance&quot; is another word formagnetic resistance, the phenomenon on which this motor is based.</P><P>This oldest electric drive concept owes its revival to the applicationof modern high-power elec-tronics and increasingly affordable microelectronics,since these features allow full power to be both derived and finely metered.The reluctance motor is thus a genuine alternative to the con-ventionaldirect-current motor.</P><P>The reluctance motors used in Necar II have several advantages. Sincethe accompanying power electronics are housed directly in the engine, separatecircuit boxes for control, protection and diagnosis systems or for sensorscan be dispensed with. As well as reducing production costs, this makesthe motor considerably smaller and lighter.<BR></TD></TR></TABLE></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><BR><IMG SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif" WIDTH="592" HEIGHT="16" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0"><TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH="550"><H5><A HREF="60923_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A> <A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="60923_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A> <A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A> </H5></TD></TR></TABLE></P><ADDRESS ALIGN=CENTER>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 10/01/1996</ADDRESS></BODY></HTML>
