<HTML>

<HEAD><TITLE>Close encounter of the third kind?</TITLE></HEAD>



<BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF">

<P>



<CENTER>



<A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A>

<A HREF="60910_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A>

<A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> 

<A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A>

<BR>



<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P>



<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Close encounter of the third kind?</B></FONT>

<P>



<table>

<TR>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380>

<A HREF="pics/60917.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/60917.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif">

<i>Stuttgart, September 17, 1996</i><br>

For ever wilt thou love, and she be fair ... No, this is not the kiss of two extraterrestrial creatures, but a new type of mixer diode produced at the Daimler-Benz Research Centre in Ulm.
<p>

Compact and micro-radar systems call for increasingly high-performance microelectronic components; on the other hand, their manufacture is to be simple and economical. These were the guiding principles for the Daimler-Benz researchers in developing the new mixer diodes for contact-free automotive sensor systems and for radiometric application in guidance and steering systems.
<p>

The researchers found the solution in the form of the mixer diode, based on gallium-arsenide. It is distinguished from comparable, conventional diodes by new heterostructures incorporating layers of thickness in the order of mere nanometres (a nanometre is one millionth of a millimetre) and containing indium near the surface. The microelectronic characteristics of the diode can thus be further improved while maintaining manufacturing costs at a low level.
<p>

Within a short time, these new structures left the confines of research and development to bring about very favourable results in the product sector. The researchers are currently preparing the diode for series production; this is opening up promising opportunities in the fields of high-frequency sensor technology and communications technology.


</TABLE>

<P><BR>



<IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P>



<TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550>

<H5><A HREF="60917_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A>

