<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Clear visibility in rain</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="60903_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Clear visibility in rain</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><A HREF="pics/60910.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/60910.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif"><i>Stuttgart, September 10, 1996</i><br>The young motorist strains to see the road in front of her. Although the windscreen wipers are operating at high speed, the water splashed up by vehicles in front prevents her from gaining a clear view of the road.<p>The reduction of so-called spray film formation is the objective of a project being carried out by researchers, aerodynamics experts and design engineers from the Daimler-Benz group. By refining and combining methods already used in spray film analysis, the scientists have developed a technique which yields both locally restricted measurements and three-dimensional, high-resolution images of the entire spray film caused by a vehicle. These measurements are assessed by the aero-dynamics engineers, after which they are incorporated into vehicle design.<p>The principal parameter used in this method is the intensity of light which is scattered when the water droplets of the spray mist are illuminated. The scientists carry out the light scattering measurements by a combination of so-called light-section technology (two-dimensional development of light rays) and video technology, which allows pictorial presentation of the measurements. Initial findings have been gained in investigations carried out in the wind tunnel, which by means of individual images above all provide locally restricted spray film measurements.<p>The light scattering measurements on the test track set out to record the entire spray film caused by a vehicle. Only the combination of local and temporal changes in the spray mist characteristics - expressed in scattered light intensities - provides an objective measure of impairment to visibility. The scientists therefore record an entire series of individual images, each of which shows the local distribution of mist intensity at a given time, i.e. at a specific distance to the vehicle.<p>The conversion of mist intensities into visibility distances permits objective evaluation of measures for the reduction of spray film formation. And less spray mist means enhanced road safety in wet conditions.</TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="60910_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="60903_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 09/10/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
