<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Cumpan - a companion in environmental protection</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="60827_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Cumpan - a companion in environmental protection</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><i>Stuttgart, September 3, 1996</i><br>On average, each German household has three different rubbish bins: for paper, for recyclable material and for other waste. Environmental protection thus starts at home, for everyone - in a relatively simple way. <p>Operating an enterprise such as a manufacturing company in an environment-friendly manner, on the other hand, is a highly complex undertaking. Assistance is now available in the form of "Cumpan", a computer programme for lifecycle assessment developed by Daimler-Benz Research in collaboration with the University of Hockenheim. The acronym "Cumpan" stands for "computergest&uuml;tze, umweltorientierte Produktanalyse" (computer-aided, environment-oriented product analysis).<p>In the first stage - abstract assessment - Cumpan registers all environmentally relevant data in connection with each stage of a product's life. This begins with the raw materials required and the energy used in obtaining them and continues through manufacture and the waste produced in the process and incorporates such matters as water pollution and noxious exhaust emissions. <p>In the subsequent environmental impact assessment, Cumpan sorts the individual items of data obtained from the abstract assessment according to their effects on the environment. These factors include contributions to the greenhouse effect or to the ozone deficiency and summer smog, ground acidity levels and fertiliser concentrations in water. The data are constantly based on the latest findings of the internationally recognised Society of Environment, Toxicology and Chemistry (SETAC) and the German Federal Environmental Office. </TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="60903_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="60827_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 09/03/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
