<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Combustion in the cold</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="60813_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Combustion in the cold</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><A HREF="pics/60820.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/60820.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif"><i>Stuttgart, August 20, 1996</i><br>Scorching summer temperatures prevail outdoors. And even in the laboratory of engineer Eberhard Holder, the mercury still indicates well over twenty degrees Celsius. In the middle of the room, however, winter seems to have broken out: small ice crystals cover the research engine with a white coating.<p>Daimler-Benz researchers are using the "deep-frozen engine" to investigate fuel combustion at temperatures as low as -20 &#176;C. But instead of transforming the laboratory into a freezer, the scientists banish fuel, air and coolant to a freezer outside the laboratory and then direct them, appropriately tempered, into the engine.<p>The advantages of this method are self-evident; the effects can be realised by relatively simple means. Fuel, air and coolant rapidly reach the desired temperature, so that according to the scientists, up to 15 measurements a day can be carried out - not to mention the considerably more pleasant working conditions made possible.<p>The cold-start investigations have been motivated by the stringent emission limits to come into force in future. Such low values cannot be attained with the catalytic converter alone, explains Holder: at low temperatures, such as prevail directly after the engine is started, catalytic converters do not yet operate optimally.<p>The research engine is a single-cylinder unit, whose characteristics have been adapted to those of a complete engine. The scientists are thus able to investigate and evaluate the cold-start and warming-up behaviour of complete engines at an early stage of development. Optical methods are being used to analyse the transportation of fuel to the engine interior.<p>The findings obtained with the research engine can be immediately incorporated in the form of improvements to the automotive engine. The arrangement and droplet spectrum of the intake valves or the air flow into the intake port, for instance, can considerably influence the exhaust values during cold starts.</TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="60820_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="60813_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 08/20/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
