<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Light materials stage a light show: laser welding technology</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="60730_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Light materials stage a light show: laser welding technology</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><A HREF="pics/60806.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/60806.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif"><i>Stuttgart, August 8, 1996</i><br>The darkness is broken by yellow and red rays of light, and then a dazzling white beam illuminates the scene once more. But there are no "ah's" and "oh's" to accompany this light show, since it is everyday routine for the Daimler-Benz researchers at Ottobrunn. <p>These weird and wonderful visual effects are a by-product of laser welding tech-nology. The special feature of this "no-touch" technique is the absence of rivets between the aluminium workpieces - a characteristic which makes this welding method indispensable in today's era of lightweight design. <p>The researchers have unravelled the mystery of the physical and material-related complexities which this new technique entails. Trouble-free laser welding is only possible when the laser beam characteristics are precisely matched to the physi-cal properties of the material.<p>In automotive manufacture, economic and ecological considerations call for a re-duction in structural weights - "lightweight design". Laser welding thus opens up new opportunities not only in the production of road vehicles, but also in the fields of rail transport and aviation.</TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="60806_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="60730_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 08/06/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
