<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>How to stay mobile in a smog alarm</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../news_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/researkl.gif"></A><A HREF="60716_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>How to stay mobile in a smog alarm</B></FONT><P><table><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380><A HREF="pics/60723.jpg"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 border=0 SRC="pics/60723.gif"></A><IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=3 HSPACE=-2 WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=80 SRC="../../icons/abstand.gif"><i>Stuttgart, July 23, 1996</i><br>To mountain-climbers, it is quite a familiar sight: the summit is bathed in sunshine, whilst the valley lies under a thick, impenetrable shroud of smoke and dirt.<p>Cities with major industrial districts and high traffic volumes are particularly affected by smog. When these towns threaten to suffocate, immediate action is called for - but until now, the individual has only been able to make a contribution at the expense of his own personal mobility: by leaving his car in the garage.<p>But this situation can soon change. With the development of an alternative drive system known as the fuel cell, the Daimler-Benz researchers have reconciled environmental compatibility with mobility. In the fuel cell, electricity is produced by electro-chemical means from hydrogen and oxygen. The only product of this reaction is pure water, which issues from the exhaust pipe in the form of vapour. The environment is thus polluted neither by carbon dioxide nor by the nitrogen oxides, and no soot particles contaminate the air. Man and nature can breathe a sigh of relief.<p>The first step into the future has already been taken: the completely pollutant-free, low-noise "Necar II" research vehicle can already be seen on the streets today. Powered by fuel cells, it provides space for six people and has an operat-ing range of over 250 kilometres. And with a top speed of 110 km/h, driving on the motorway is no problem either.<p>Developments are continuing. Daimler-Benz will first realise this emission-free drive system in urban buses; and by the year 2010, fuel cell drive is expected to be ready for installation in the A-class vehicle.</TABLE><P><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="60723_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../news_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Research &amp; Technology</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="60716_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>  <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 07/23/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
