<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Files and Documents: Technology '96</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="docs_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/docskl.gif"></A><A HREF="../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+3><B>Technology '96</B></FONT><P><TABLE><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275 valign=top> The Technology '96 Magazine reports on interesting technological developments drawn from the entire Daimler-Benz Group. Here, you can download the individual reports in<br> <TD width=20><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275 valign=top>the original layout-with complete access to all text. However, you will need the <A HREF="#acroread">Acrobat viewer</A> in order to read the files. You can also order the brochure in <A HREF="../order/order_e.htm">printed form</A>.<TR><TD><BR></TABLE><IMG WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../lines/db_250.gif"><P><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=center WIDTH=275><b><i><a href="files/tech96/3_e.pdf">Editorial</i></b></A><br>Prof. Dr.-Ing. Hartmut Weule<br> (33 kB)<br></TABLE><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><b>Vehicles<br><i><a href="files/tech96/6-13_e.pdf">Wanted: The Car of the Future</i></b></A><br>Researchers are already workingon the car of the future. Although,no-one knows what such a vehiclewill look like, some things areclear: it will be greener, morecomfortable - and consume less.</i><br> (612 kB)<br><td width=20><TD VALIGN=TOP align=left width=275><b>Alternative Drives<br><i><a href="files/tech96/14-19_e.pdf">Exhaust-Free Driving</i></b></A><br>Bang on schedule, Daimler-BenzResearch is unveiling itssecond fuel cell vehicle - and awhole range of spectaculartechnological improvements.<br> (699 kB)<tr><td><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><b>Traffic<br><i><a href="files/tech96/22-26_e.pdf">Roll On-Tomorrow</i></b></A><br>The nightmare scenario of ever-increasingtraffic gradually chokingboth itself and the environment nowhas an alternative - the Daimler-Benz concept of Intelligent Mobility.<br> (850 kB)<br><td width=20><TD VALIGN=TOP align=left width=275><b>Aviation<br><i><a href="files/tech96/28-32_e.pdf">Airbus of Tomorrow</i></b></A><br>"Adaptive Wings" - a key projectfrom Dasa and the DLR -will enable aircraft to bettermatch their performance tothe prevailing flight situation.And with air traffic volumesset to double over the next 15years, this new developmentcould help curb the expectedincrease in pollution.<br> (266 kB)<tr><td><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><b>Aviation<br><i><a href="files/tech96/34-39_e.pdf">Building the Big Birds</i></b></A><br>Hamburg has now joined Toulouse as an established finalassembly location for the Airbus. Without conscientiousplanning and the finest precision, getting the high-techbirds ready for takeoff would be well-nigh impossible.<br> (497 kB)<td width=20><TD VALIGN=TOP align=left width=275><b>Space Flight<br><i><a href="files/tech96/40-51_e.pdf">The View from Space</i></b></A><br>Without remote Earth sensing, it would be impossible to investigate the global problems of "spaceship Earth" as it journeys through the universe. However, exploring our planetary neighbors and the solar system itself is also important if we are to better understand the world in which we live.</i><br> (1.390 kB)<br><tr><td><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><b>Space Flight<br><i><a href="files/tech96/52-57_e.pdf">Giving Europe a Boost/i></b></A><br>The failed maiden launch represents just a temporary setback to the European Ariane 5 program. In future, this new generation of carrier rockets will not only be able to ferry several heavy satellites into space simultaneously - it will achieve this feat at a more competitive price than its predecessors.<br> (418 kB)<td width=20><TD VALIGN=TOP align=left width=275><b>Microsystems<br><i><a href="files/tech96/60-67_e.pdf">Solutions from the Land of Lilliput</i></b></A><br>Microelectronic chips are growing up - and acquiring eyes, ears and hands in the process. In the guise of microsystemsscarcely larger than a grain of sand, they can feel pressure andacceleration, see images, act as tools, and accommodate tinymotors. The range of potential applications is vast, extendingfrom future cars and aircraft to TV and endoscopes.Microelectronic chips are growing up-and acquiring eyes, ears and hands in the process. In the guise of microsystemsscarcely larger than a grain of sand, they can feel pressure andacceleration, see images, act as tools, and accommodate tinymotors. The range of potential applications is vast, extendingfrom future cars and aircraft to TV and endoscopes.<br> (637 kB)<br><tr><td><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><b>Electronics<br><i><a href="files/tech96/68-73_e.pdf">Bring the Big Laser Screens Back Home</i></b></A><br>Will the new "Laser Displays" from Daimler-Benz andSchneider be the "screen stars" of tomorrow?<br> (382 kB)<td width=20><TD VALIGN=TOP align=left width=275><b>Automation<br><i><a href="files/tech96/74-77_e.pdf">The Last Post for Unsorted Mail</i></b></A><br>Airmail or postcard, newspaper orCD: Whatever the format,wherever the address, the new automatedsystems from AEG Electrocomare helping sort out themail in post offices throughoutthe world.</i><br> (374 kB)<br><tr><td><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275><b>Informations Technology<br><i><a href="files/tech96/78-81_e.pdf">Together to the Teraflop</i></b></A><br>In a unique collaboration of public and private enterprise, debisSystemhaus, Porsche AG and the state have joined forces to launch a pilot project in Stuttgart: a supercomputer center for commerce and science.<br> (274 kB)<br><td width=20><TD VALIGN=TOP align=left width=275><b>Society and Technology<br><i><a href="files/tech96/82-85_e.pdf">Moving with the Times</i></b></A><br>"Tomorrow's products for tomorrow's customers," mustbe the slogan of every forward-looking company. But justwhat will the needs and desires of tomorrow'scustomers actually look like? The Daimler-Benz Berlin-basedresearch group "Society and Technology" iscurrently investigating changing lifestyles and their resultingimpact on product development.<br> (302 kB)<br><tr><td></TABLE><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=center WIDTH=275><b>R&amp;D Management<br><i><a href="files/tech96/86-89_e.pdf">The Customer is King</i></b></A><br>Why do Germans find exploiting research results so difficult? Why is the successful market launch of many technological developments so often left to Japanese companies? To remedy this situation, Prof. Hartmut Weule, technology boss of Daimler-Benz, is putting his faith in a new culture of innovation.<br> (214 kB)</TABLE><P>    <A NAME="acroread"></A><IMG WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../lines/db_250.gif"><P><TABLE><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=center WIDTH=450>To be able to take advantage of this offer, you will require<br> the appropriate program or a viewer.<br>When installing please follow the instructions described in the readme-files.<p><i><A HREF="viewers/english/acroread.exe"><B>For PC, 1.492 kB</B><br><A HREF="viewers/english/ACROREAD.MAC.hqx"><B>For Mac, 3.778 kB</B></i></A><br>Viewers for UNIX are available <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/Acrobat/freeread.html">at Adobe</A><br></TABLE><P><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=55