<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>At a Glance: More about debis System Solutions</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../group_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/komp_kl.gif"></A><A HREF="system_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>More about debis System Solutions</B></FONT><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=380>debis Systemhaus was established in 1990 to offer services in the field of information technology (IT) that are not tied to the products of any individual manufacturer. In order to strengthen the company's market position in Germany and to obtain access to international markets, debis Systemhaus entered into a strategic alliance with <A HREF="http://www.cgs.fr">Cap Gemini Sogeti</A> in 1992.<p>The range of products offered by Germany's leading independent IT service company addresses the specific needs of each sector of the economy, and covers the entire spectrum of information processing. Through its core competences in consultancy, development and marketing, debis Systemhaus is in a position to offer its customers information technology solutions that will transform and revitalise their businesses - and all from a single source. As an example, debis Systemhaus will take over responsibility for the maintenance and servicing of applications systems. Business Transformation Services will not only design, implement and service the customer's IT-related corporate functions - for instance the computer centre and network services - but also take over operational responsibility. "The crucial advantage for the customer," says Karl-Heinz Achinger, the member of the Board of Management of debis AG responsible for Systemhaus, "is that on the one hand he receives high-value services which can be provided with flexibility and yet within planned time schedules and budgets; whilst on the other hand he can rely on the corporate strength and expertise of one of the biggest suppliers of comprehensive IT services in the European market that is not tied to any specific manufacturer."<p>In 1994 debis Systemhaus with its staff of more than 6,000 achieved total turnover of DM 1.8 billion in this market, which will generate some DM 22 billion worth of business in Germany  this year. </TABLE><P><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="syste2_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../group_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>At a Glance</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="system_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Up</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>   <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 04/11/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
