<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Environmental Report `96 - Highlights: A Clean Plate</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/envirokl.gif"></A><A HREF="../schlag_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="17_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><font size=+2><b>A Clean Plate</b></font><p><TABLE><TR><TD ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=275 valign=top>Dasa's sparkling new electroplating plant in Augsburg is a paragon of environmental propriety.<br><TD width=20><TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=275 valign=top>Baths, pollution levels, discharges, construction philosophy-all are taking a hand in cleaning up this once dirty act.<tr><td><br></TABLE><p><table><tr><td valign=top align=left width=380><a href="../pics/16.jpg"><img align=left vspace=3 hspace=-2 width=100 height=80 border=0 src="../pics/16.gif"></a><img align=left vspace=3 hspace=-2 width=6 height=80 src="../../icons/abstand.gif">The electroplating shop is a toxic place, and often a potential hazard to the environment. Inside, metal components are submerged in baths of highly concentrated and often poisonous metal salts which, under the influence of an electric current, yield elemental metals that are then deposited as a shining coating on the surfaces of the immersed parts.<p>So far so good, but once the baths are exhausted, the problems really begin. At this stage, although the metal salt concentrations in the baths are too low for electroplating, they are still way too high for the solutions to be simply poured down the drain. Disposal of the poisonous brew is thus a major headache. Of course, the most elegant answer is to stretch, save, and reprocess the baths so that the residues are minimized.<p>This recycling philosophy has been thoroughly taken on board at Daimler-Benz Aerospace's (Dasa) Augsburg electroplating facility, which is primarily responsible for chrome-anodizing aluminum and pickling titanium. The facility, which was commissioned in 1995, includes the following features:&bull;  The baths remain "fresh" for longer thanks to innovations such as a cascade washing process, which returns media carry-over; edge-spraying equipment fed from the subsequent wash bath; evaporation techniques for concentrating and recycling drag-out rinse water and process solutions; and, finally, an ion exchange plant to remove polluting trivalent metal ions from the anodizing baths.<p>Compared to the old, closed facility, the waste-water discharges are down to just fifteen percent of their original value. Such advances have been achieved courtesy of a multiple rinsing technique, ion exchanger cycles, settable drip times, spray protection, and reclaiming materials.Moreover, the pollutant levels which are contained in the remaining effluents can now be reduced by more than 90 percent thanks to the use of a selective ion-exchange plant, which binds the dissolved metals.</table><p><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="16_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Environment</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../ub96_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Environmental Report '96</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../schlag_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Highlights</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="17_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>   <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 08/06/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
