<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Environmental Report `96 - Projects: Powerful Sprinter</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/envirokl.gif"></A><A HREF="../projek_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="27_2_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><font size=+2><b>Powerful Sprinter</b></font><p><table><tr><td valign=top align=left width=380><a href="../pics/27_1.jpg"><img align=left vspace=3 hspace=-2 width=100 height=80 border=0 src="../pics/27_1.gif"></a><img align=left vspace=3 hspace=-2 width=6 height=80 src="../../icons/abstand.gif">They look completely normal, the six "Sprinter" vans belonging to the Cologne firm Rheinische Energie AG (rhenag), and the two vehicles from Hermes. Only the letters NGT emblazoned upon the gleaming coachwork of the vehicles hint at their secret-Natural Gas Technology. Behind the abbreviation is a new injection system for natural gas engines, which is comparable to a gasoline injection system. Until now, gas-driven vehicles have always used continuous injection-similar to the carburetor principle in a gasoline engine. The gasoline PMS engine control system software has now been adapted to the special requirements of a gas engine. Not only is the technology simpler, it also extorts even lower emission values from the already low-emission gas drive. In the words of Rolf Bartke, head of the Transport department at Mercedes-Benz, it is "the fossil-fuel-based drive technology with the lowest pollutant emissions." <p>Moreover, despite its low emissions, the NGT Sprinter is almost as powerful as a comparable gasoline-powered vehicle. The pressurized gas container can either be fitted under the floor (130-liter version) or in the load bay (160-liter version). The range depends on the capacity of the gas container-some 250 to 300 kilometers in the case of the 160 liter-and, on a liter for liter basis, is double that of previous gas-powered vehicles.</table><p><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="27_1_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Environment</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../ub96_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Environmental Report '96</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../projek_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Projects</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="27_2_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>   <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 08/06/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
