<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Environmental Report `96 - Highlights: No-Smoker Trains</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/envirokl.gif"></A><A HREF="../schlag_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="14_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><font size=+2><b>No-Smoker Trains</b></font><p><table><tr><td valign=top align=left width=380><a href="../pics/13_6.jpg"><img align=left vspace=3 hspace=-2 width=100 height=80 border=0 src="../pics/13_6.gif"></a><img align=left vspace=3 hspace=-2 width=6 height=80 src="../../icons/abstand.gif">Cleaner and more economical diesel locomotives with lower exhaust emissions will soon be rolling down the lines of the Deutsche Bahn AG-the German national railroad company-thanks to a retrofitting concept which has been developed by the Daimler-Benz subsidiary Motoren- und Turbinen-Union MTU for the 218-Series diesel locomotives, all of which are to be modernized over the coming years. Not only the environment, but the passengers too can now breathe a sigh of relief: repeated complaints about the smell of exhaust emissions from the 218-Series percolating into air-conditioned trains with their air-intakes on the car roofs should now be a thing of the past. These tried-and-tested locomotives-500 of which were delivered with engines from MTU between 1970 and 1979-have clocked up over three million kilometers of service, and still look capable of quite a few more. A prototype has already demonstrated the success of the locomotive rejuvenation procedure, which is primarily based on optimizing the combustion process. This is accomplished by means of an improved fuel injection system, modifications to the shape of the combustion chamber, and a configuration incorporating a turbocharger. The drop in exhaust emissions is impressive: carbon monoxide has been reduced by two-thirds; hydrocarbons by 84 percent; and soot by 86 percent. Test journeys conducted in the course of scheduled service have also revealed that diesel consumption of the rejuvenated locomotive has been cut by a factor of more than ten percent.</table><p><br><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=550><H5><A HREF="13_6_g.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Deutsch</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../index_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Home</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Environment</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../ub96_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Environmental Report '96</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../schlag_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Highlights</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="14_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Next</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Search</I>&nbsp;]</A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Dialog</I>&nbsp;]</A>   <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm">[&nbsp;<I>Help</I>&nbsp;]</A></H5></TABLE><ADDRESS>&copy; Daimler-Benz, last update: 08/06/1996</ADDRESS><P></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
