<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Environmental Report '96 - Energy and Water Consumption</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/envirokl.gif"></A><A HREF="../schlag_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="emiss_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=360><font size=+2><b>Energy and Water Consumption</b></font><p>From 1995 onwards, the calculations for total fossil energy consumption included for the first time test stand and driving test consumption figures for diesel, SI, and aircraft fuels. Comparisons between the overall figure and data from previous years must therefore take this extra change of 237 Gigawatt hours (Gwh) into account. As a result of a general growth in production, total consumption of fossil and electric energy (externally generated) plus district heating grew by 1.75 percent.<p>Although total water consumption fell during the year under review, there were extreme variations between operations. For the first time, the Optoelectronics and Vacuum Electronics division has been included in the AEG statistics, which has led to a rise in water consumption of almost 500000 cubic meters for production in the micro-electronics area. MTU-M&uuml;nchen's new continuous cooling system, which uses spring water, consumed 900000 cubic meters. In addition, MTU-Friedrichshafen used an extra 500000 cubic meters of cooling water. On the other side of the balance sheet, around 900000 cubic meters was saved at the Mercedes-Benz plant in W&ouml;rth thanks to conversion of the compressed air unit from continuous-flow to closed-cycle cooling. The Rail division at ASF N&uuml;rnberg and Hennigsdorf also cut water consumption by 160000 cubic meters. Further savings were achieved at Dasa through modifications to the electroplating shop in Augsburg.</table><p><br><table><tr><td><td><td align=middle colspan=7 valign=bottom><b>Electrical Energy</b><tr><td><td><td align=middle colspan=3 valign=bottom><b>Externally generated</b><td><td align=middle colspan=3 valign=bottom><b>Generated in house</b><tr><td valign=bottom><font size=-1>Consumption in GWh</font><td><td align=right width=60 valign=bottom><b>1993</b><td align=right width=60 valign=bottom><b>1994</b><td align=right width=60 valign=bottom><b>1995</b><td><td align=right width=60 valign=bottom><b>1993</b><td align=right width=60 valign=bottom><b>1994</b><td align=right width=60 valign=bottom><b>1995</b><tr><td align=right width=100 valign=top><td><tr><td colspan=9><hr><tr><tr><td align=right><B>AEG</B><td><td align=right>263<td align=right>212<td align=right>244<td><td align=right>24<td align=right>26<td align=right>29<tr><td align=right><B>DASA</B><td><td align=right>552<td align=right>556<td align=right>456<td><td align=right>12<td align=right>16<td align=right>11<tr><td align=right><B>debis</B><td><td align=right>14<td align=right>6<td align=right>49<td><td align=right><td align=right><td align=right><tr><td align=right><B>DBAG</B><td><td align=right>30<td align=right>31<td align=right>33<td><td align=right><td align=right><td align=right><tr><td align=right><B>MBAG</B><td><td align=right>2077<td align=right>2188<td align=right>2225<td><td align=right>196<