<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Environmental Report '96 - Wastes</TITLE></HEAD><BODY background="../../icons/db_back1.jpg" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#2060A0" VLINK="#606060" ALINK="#E0E0FF"><P><CENTER><A HREF="../../index_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=89 HEIGHT=33 SRC="../../icons/db_home.gif"></A><A HREF="../envir_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/envirokl.gif"></A><A HREF="../schlag_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_up.gif"></A><A HREF="energy_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/menu_rig.gif"></A><A HREF="../../search/search_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/db_such.gif"></A><A HREF="../../mail/mail_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/mailkl.gif"></A> <A HREF="../../help/help_e.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=54 HEIGHT=44 SRC="../../icons/helpkl.gif"></A><BR><IMG WIDTH=592 HEIGHT=16 SRC="../../lines/db_592.gif"><P><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=360><font size=+2><b>Wastes</b></font><p>Waste figures have been sinking across the board for some years now. This is particularly evident in the area of "Commercial Wastes similar to Domestic Garbage"-above all at AEG and Dasa. The increase in this type of waste at Mercedes-Benz, on the other hand, was the result of almost 10000 extra tonnes of foundry sand used in axle production at Mannheim compared to 1994. However, increased recycling will significantly reduce foundry sand waste in the years to come.<p>A fall of over 16 percent has been recorded in the highly sensitive area of "Wastes requiring Special Monitoring," while the figures for "Recycled Waste Materials" also incorporate residues which were able to be sold, such as over 400000 tonnes of scrap metal. AEG and Dasa logged a total of DM 8.3 million in credits for sales of scrap metal.</table><p><br><table><tr><td><td><td align=middle colspan=3 valign=bottom><b>Recycled waste<br> materials</b><td><td align=middle colspan=3 valign